Alright, I'm just gonna tell you, the answer
is: you could call it a D sharp or a little

00:03:54.620 --> 00:04:02.140
bit to the right of D, or you could call it
an E flat - a little bit to the left of E.

00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:06.870
Okay? So that's pretty much how you can figure
out all the names of the notes here so we've

00:04:06.870 --> 00:04:18.650
got C D E F G A B C and if we look at this
note we have C sharp or D flat. We have D

00:04:18.650 --> 00:04:29.130
sharp or E flat. F sharp of G flat. G sharp
or A flat. And A sharp or B flat. And that's

00:04:29.130 --> 00:04:33.810
it, those are the names of the notes. you
can do that in any octave, so C C C and all

00:04:33.810 --> 00:04:37.210
the way up and all the way down, they'er labeled
